WEBVTT

00:10.610 --> 00:13.013
♪♪♪

00:29.496 --> 00:31.965
Beatriz?

00:32.031 --> 00:33.600
I've been told you're looking
for information

00:33.666 --> 00:36.403
about someone who used
to work here, am I right?

00:36.469 --> 00:37.871
My mother,
Sara Ballester.

00:39.372 --> 00:40.573
Come with me.

00:47.614 --> 00:50.483
This place has been closed
to the public for years,

00:50.550 --> 00:54.387
but it was crowded
back when it was a luxury spa.

00:54.487 --> 00:57.023
We keep a record of each one
of them here.

00:57.123 --> 00:58.324
What did she do for a living?

00:58.391 --> 01:01.895
- I don't know.
- We'll find out soon enough.

01:09.002 --> 01:10.470
Please, wait here.
I'll go get a flashlight.

01:10.570 --> 01:10.970
All right.

01:52.879 --> 01:54.147
[door creaking, slamming]

01:54.247 --> 01:55.415
[lighter hitting floor]

01:55.482 --> 01:56.950
[panting]

02:07.794 --> 02:09.362
- [blowing]
- [gasping]

02:09.429 --> 02:10.730
[screaming]

02:10.797 --> 02:14.334
Push, push, push.
Come on.

02:14.400 --> 02:15.368
Very good.
Please, breathe.

02:15.435 --> 02:17.804
Breathe, okay?
You're doing great.

02:17.871 --> 02:19.806
You have to continue, ma'am.

02:19.873 --> 02:23.610
- Yes, you're almost there.
- [screaming]

02:23.676 --> 02:24.911
Come on, you can do it.
Just listen to me.

02:26.913 --> 02:29.315
You're doing great,
just keep pushing.

02:32.452 --> 02:33.887
Should I bring the equipment?

02:38.725 --> 02:40.360
[sobbing]
Mario.

02:40.426 --> 02:43.530
I'm sorry.

02:43.596 --> 02:44.998
[grunting]

02:49.302 --> 02:51.671
[screaming]

03:04.384 --> 03:06.786
Mario.

03:06.886 --> 03:08.288
Stay here with the girls.

03:08.354 --> 03:09.889
MARIO: Why am I the only one
who doesn't know?

03:09.956 --> 03:10.590
Please, Mario, stop.
Mario, please, come on.

03:10.690 --> 03:12.792
[overlapping shouting]

03:12.892 --> 03:13.760
Mario, look at the fucking road!

03:13.826 --> 03:16.596
Jesus, Mario.
Mario!

04:14.520 --> 04:16.589
[doorbell ringing]

04:23.029 --> 04:24.230
I'm sorry.

04:26.399 --> 04:27.033
I'm very sorry.

04:32.038 --> 04:34.307
Hurry, hurry, hurry.
He's coming.

04:34.407 --> 04:36.709
[overlapping shouting]

04:38.144 --> 04:41.481
Diego! Diego! Diego!

04:41.547 --> 04:41.948
Tell me this isn't true.

04:44.350 --> 04:44.917
Diego!

04:47.287 --> 04:49.589
[overlapping shouting continues]

04:53.092 --> 04:55.828
REPORTER:A savage crime
committed

04:55.928 --> 04:57.630
<i>by an unscrupulous human,
Diego Morte,</i>

04:57.730 --> 05:00.733
<i>the monster of Almanzora.</i>

05:00.800 --> 05:02.168
<i>He has been
arrested today</i>

05:02.235 --> 05:04.637
<i>as the main suspect
of kidnapping and murdering</i>

05:04.704 --> 05:06.839
<i>three innocent girls.</i>

05:06.906 --> 05:10.176
<i>Inside the port boathouse
to which only he had access,</i>

05:10.243 --> 05:13.146
<i>evidence of human remains
were found hidden</i>

05:13.246 --> 05:15.948
<i>in a freezer, in addition
to numerous fingerprints</i>

05:16.049 --> 05:17.183
<i>of the victims.</i>

05:17.283 --> 05:19.552
<i>Flammable material
has also been found</i>

05:19.652 --> 05:21.154
<i>which may tie Diego Morte
directly</i>

05:21.254 --> 05:24.023
<i>to the Paraiso arson
in which four boys</i>

05:24.123 --> 05:27.327
<i>have also died,
including his own stepson,</i>

05:27.393 --> 05:30.063
<i>as well as the brother
of one of the victims.</i>

05:32.732 --> 05:34.233
Zeta, wait.

05:39.205 --> 05:41.507
[motorcycle starting]

05:46.879 --> 05:49.449
<i>But why did he force
the three girls</i>

05:49.515 --> 05:52.352
<i>to record a messagea few
hours before killing them?</i>

05:52.452 --> 05:55.588
<i>What kind of harassment
did he subject them to?</i>

05:55.688 --> 05:57.090
<i>Were they tortured?</i>

05:57.156 --> 06:01.160
<i>These questions
still remain unanswered</i>

06:01.227 --> 06:05.832
<i>in a case that has kept the
whole country in suspense.</i>

06:05.932 --> 06:07.767
<i>Marina Santolaya,
from Almanzora</i>

06:07.834 --> 06:08.968
<i>for the special report
on the Almanzora girls.</i>

06:22.348 --> 06:24.117
I'm really sorry, Mario.

06:31.224 --> 06:31.891
You don't have
to do this, sir.

07:12.932 --> 07:15.001
[Mario screaming]

07:36.055 --> 07:39.625
[bell tolling]

07:58.144 --> 08:00.446
[snoring]

08:14.794 --> 08:17.563
Uh, did you know Ghost Riders
can't see us in the light

08:17.630 --> 08:19.398
and it causes them
to disintegrate?

08:19.465 --> 08:22.134
It's like-- like the noise
to Dan Defensor,

08:22.201 --> 08:24.437
or Superman with kryptonite.

08:24.504 --> 08:26.806
What if that's
their weakness?

08:26.873 --> 08:28.207
Shut it.

08:30.943 --> 08:32.645
We should come up with...

08:32.712 --> 08:34.080
I think we should come up
with a weapon

08:34.146 --> 08:35.948
to fight the Ghost Riders.

08:36.048 --> 08:41.087
The weapon could be a laser beam
or a lightsaber.

08:43.189 --> 08:44.690
Photon cannon.

08:59.872 --> 09:01.307
I'm speaking with Javi.

09:44.884 --> 09:46.452
They were shaved.

09:47.887 --> 09:50.523
They were forced to eat bugs.

09:50.590 --> 09:52.892
Just to end up murdered
inside of a freezer?

09:54.827 --> 09:56.095
It's not the girls.

09:57.597 --> 09:59.231
Those aren't their bodies.

10:01.000 --> 10:02.802
Then whose are they?

10:02.868 --> 10:04.303
OLIVIA: Hey, you!

10:06.305 --> 10:07.406
Yeah, you!

10:10.276 --> 10:13.112
You talked to my grandma last
before she died.

10:13.212 --> 10:14.480
What did she say?

10:17.750 --> 10:19.285
What did she say?

10:19.352 --> 10:20.953
Geez, Quino.

10:21.053 --> 10:22.388
What did she tell you, Javi?

10:24.523 --> 10:28.761
Javier, you're telling me
all about it at my house.

10:28.828 --> 10:30.396
No, we are going now.

10:31.430 --> 10:32.632
Javier!

10:38.704 --> 10:40.640
Yeah, sure.
Don't worry about it.

10:40.706 --> 10:42.508
Yeah, I'll call you back.
Bye.

10:46.312 --> 10:49.315
As I was saying, at that age
they just want some attention.

10:50.383 --> 10:51.517
You won't look anyway?

10:53.052 --> 10:54.553
I know you must be worried,

10:54.654 --> 10:56.956
but let's wait
for a while to see.

10:57.023 --> 10:58.491
She's been missing
since last night.

10:58.557 --> 10:59.592
No, she spent
the night elsewhere.

10:59.692 --> 11:00.893
Why don't you get it?
She's diabetic.

11:00.960 --> 11:04.463
She'd never leave unannounced.

11:04.563 --> 11:05.831
When was the last time
you spoke to her?

11:05.931 --> 11:07.400
[phone ringing]

11:07.466 --> 11:08.768
Hello?

11:08.834 --> 11:11.070
I'll be right with you.

11:13.072 --> 11:14.774
She had low blood sugar
yesterday

11:14.840 --> 11:16.175
and she stayed
resting at home.

11:17.209 --> 11:18.344
And then what?

11:20.079 --> 11:21.681
Nothing important.

11:21.747 --> 11:25.084
She was overwhelmed
with family matters.

11:25.151 --> 11:27.386
What kind of matters?
Did you argue?

11:29.755 --> 11:32.425
My daughter
didn't escape from home.

11:32.525 --> 11:33.826
MARIANO: Sir?

11:33.926 --> 11:35.761
The forensics from Madrid
have arrived.

11:35.828 --> 11:38.631
Please, go home.
You should wait by the phone.

11:38.731 --> 11:40.066
She will call.

12:04.924 --> 12:08.360
[Roca singing in Spanish]

12:10.196 --> 12:11.864
[girl singing along in Spanish]

12:14.166 --> 12:16.669
[laughing]
Well, well.

12:16.769 --> 12:18.838
Did your father
teach you that song?

12:18.904 --> 12:21.273
- Huh?
- No, my mommy did.

12:21.373 --> 12:23.843
[laughing]
Shall I tell you a secret?

12:23.909 --> 12:26.212
That's the song your father
and I used to sing

12:26.278 --> 12:27.279
to the pretty girls
in the army.

12:27.346 --> 12:29.915
Mm-hmm.

12:30.015 --> 12:32.985
SARA: Mario?
Mario, what's wrong?

12:33.085 --> 12:34.587
You're pretty.

12:34.687 --> 12:36.155
Stay here with the girls.

12:36.255 --> 12:38.090
- Sara--
- Mario, Mario, listen to me.

12:38.157 --> 12:39.592
- What is it?
SARA: Please, tell me something.

12:39.692 --> 12:40.960
What happened back there?

12:51.771 --> 12:53.205
JAVI: I'm not telling you
who they are.

12:53.272 --> 12:54.306
I promised your grandma
I'd keep you out of this.

12:54.406 --> 12:57.276
OLIVIA: I asked,
where are these people?

12:57.376 --> 12:58.911
JAVI: I'm not telling you,
they're too powerful.

12:59.011 --> 13:02.114
- They'll kill you.
- That's my fucking problem.

13:02.214 --> 13:04.383
You find them,
and then what?

13:04.483 --> 13:05.684
Huh?
What will you do?

13:05.751 --> 13:07.153
You'll be all alone.

13:07.253 --> 13:09.488
We don't even know
how to kill them.

13:09.555 --> 13:11.991
Well, according to
the notebook here,

13:12.091 --> 13:13.759
only the Chosen One
with his light

13:13.826 --> 13:16.195
and infinite power can do it.

13:16.295 --> 13:18.964
OLIVIA: Who are they?
How the hell do I find them?

13:19.031 --> 13:20.666
JAVI: I'm not telling you,
Olivia.

13:20.766 --> 13:22.935
Just forget all about it.

13:23.002 --> 13:25.437
OLIVIA: They killed her, Javi.

13:25.504 --> 13:28.874
They pushed my grandma
down the fucking stairs.

13:28.974 --> 13:31.076
Don't ask me to forget it.

13:31.143 --> 13:34.413
Those scumbags
will pay for it.

13:38.150 --> 13:41.053
All we know is that
they live among us.

13:42.922 --> 13:44.523
And they look like old people
through the mirrors.

13:44.590 --> 13:46.559
ISIDRO: Olivia!

13:46.625 --> 13:48.027
You have a phone call!

13:52.565 --> 13:53.866
Couldn't you keep
your mouth shut?

13:55.868 --> 13:58.437
Where's Alvaro?

13:58.504 --> 13:58.971
He was right here.

14:01.507 --> 14:02.908
It's Bea.

14:04.910 --> 14:06.345
She's disappeared.

14:07.613 --> 14:10.716
PAULA: Samuel, I found it.
It was a cicada.

14:10.783 --> 14:12.952
Why the hell would Malena
have a cicada in her pocket?

14:13.052 --> 14:15.120
SAMUEL:<i> Well,</i>
<i>it makes sense.</i>

14:15.187 --> 14:17.289
[line disconnecting,
beeping]

14:17.356 --> 14:17.890
Shit.

14:29.535 --> 14:31.871
[line ringing]

14:34.673 --> 14:36.242
What makes sense?

14:36.308 --> 14:38.043
SAMUEL:The protein
of the future.

14:38.110 --> 14:40.713
<i>The ultimate nutrient source
for humans.</i>

14:40.813 --> 14:42.915
Are they feeding them insects?

14:43.015 --> 14:44.583
<i>Well, it's a no-brainer.</i>

14:44.683 --> 14:46.485
<i>But you haven't asked
the right question.</i>

14:46.552 --> 14:48.087
What question?

14:49.922 --> 14:51.924
<i>What for?</i>

14:51.991 --> 14:52.925
<i>What do they want
to do to them?</i>

14:55.427 --> 14:57.796
[shaver buzzing]

15:36.335 --> 15:38.370
You look gorgeous.

15:38.437 --> 15:38.971
[spitting]

15:42.675 --> 15:44.543
You may take her now.

15:44.643 --> 15:46.078
No! No!
No, I'm begging you.

15:46.145 --> 15:48.914
Please, don't take me.
Where are you taking me?

15:49.014 --> 15:50.683
Please, let me go.
Please, don't take me.

15:50.749 --> 15:51.951
Let me go!

16:28.587 --> 16:30.756
Go. Go, go!
How do you feel?

16:30.856 --> 16:33.592
[reporters shouting]

16:33.692 --> 16:35.561
I wanna hear
how you feel about this.

16:35.627 --> 16:38.330
You husband has killed your son.

16:38.397 --> 16:40.432
[overlapping shouting]

16:40.532 --> 16:42.668
Were you aware he was up
to something this awful?

16:42.768 --> 16:43.869
[overlapping shouting continues]

16:48.607 --> 16:50.009
[overlapping chatter continues]

17:19.204 --> 17:20.506
[knocking]

17:24.943 --> 17:28.313
You have to--
you have to sign this.

17:28.414 --> 17:30.082
It's the death certificate.

18:16.628 --> 18:18.997
[retching, coughing]

18:24.803 --> 18:28.107
RAMON: Mario, are you okay?

18:28.207 --> 18:30.476
[toilet flushing]

18:41.720 --> 18:43.355
Do you want me to go
and get you something

18:43.455 --> 18:44.823
like chamomile tea?

18:52.231 --> 18:53.432
I'm sorry, my friend.

18:53.532 --> 18:55.000
[thud]

19:18.757 --> 19:20.592
Why are you here?

19:26.231 --> 19:28.367
I need to see the eyes
my daughter saw

19:28.433 --> 19:29.835
before she died.

19:31.470 --> 19:33.705
Look at me.

19:35.607 --> 19:36.909
Look at me.

19:44.516 --> 19:45.884
What are you doing?

19:45.951 --> 19:47.853
I told you
to look at me.

19:51.990 --> 19:55.561
[door rattling,
knocking]

19:55.627 --> 19:58.530
RAMON: Mario.
Mario, open the door.

19:58.597 --> 19:58.864
Do it now.

20:01.200 --> 20:02.367
Shoot me!

20:02.434 --> 20:04.203
Damn it, shoot me now, Mario!

20:04.269 --> 20:05.837
- Ah!
- Shoot me now!

20:07.973 --> 20:10.309
[grunting]

20:48.947 --> 20:51.350
♪♪♪

22:50.202 --> 22:52.504
[rustling, scratching]

23:01.012 --> 23:01.880
OLIVIA: Holy fucking shit!

23:08.487 --> 23:09.988
QUINO: What are you doing
down there?

23:10.088 --> 23:12.591
This is where Bea
keeps important things.

23:12.691 --> 23:15.127
[bang]
Ah! Fuck! Shit.

23:24.603 --> 23:26.671
She was going on and on
about her past,

23:26.772 --> 23:28.840
and I didn't care.

23:28.907 --> 23:30.809
But, I have a feeling
her disappearance

23:30.876 --> 23:33.612
has something to do with that.

23:34.713 --> 23:36.047
With what?

23:45.757 --> 23:47.426
That one there
is my mother.

23:47.526 --> 23:50.028
OLIVIA: And the one next to her
is Bea's mother.

23:50.128 --> 23:53.198
I think they were good friends,
and they died on the same day.

23:53.265 --> 23:55.667
And Bea thought
it had something to do

23:55.767 --> 23:57.736
with what happened between
her father and yours,

23:57.803 --> 24:00.705
and then she found this.

24:00.806 --> 24:03.241
That's right, I remember this.
She stole it from the library.

24:06.011 --> 24:07.746
OLIVIA: Did they both work
at this place?

24:12.717 --> 24:15.587
Isn't this the spa
that was near Villajoyosa?

24:18.223 --> 24:19.424
What if she went to this place?

24:19.524 --> 24:21.960
JAVI: Impossible.

24:22.027 --> 24:23.528
What is it?

24:27.566 --> 24:29.634
Well, we know who has Bea.

24:29.734 --> 24:31.770
And we know where.

24:31.837 --> 24:33.905
We need to warn Costa
right away.

24:39.878 --> 24:41.513
[struggling]

24:43.248 --> 24:45.984
[door unlocking,
keys jingling]

24:51.156 --> 24:53.525
[footsteps]

25:24.256 --> 25:25.223
[shrieking]

25:25.323 --> 25:27.626
Bea. Bea.

25:27.726 --> 25:29.427
Bea!

25:29.528 --> 25:31.963
- Sandra?
- You're okay, we're here.

25:32.030 --> 25:35.000
[all sobbing]

25:35.066 --> 25:37.135
Are you okay?

25:37.202 --> 25:39.571
[sobbing continues]

25:44.643 --> 25:46.645
[camera clicking]

25:46.711 --> 25:48.146
REPORTER: There he is.
Mario.

25:48.246 --> 25:49.481
Mario, would you like
to give us any comment?

25:49.548 --> 25:50.916
Mr. Merino, how are you feeling?

25:51.016 --> 25:52.450
Do you think the police
could have done more

25:52.517 --> 25:54.052
to save your daughter?

25:54.119 --> 25:56.588
Could you tell us when and where
you plan to bury Sandra?

25:56.688 --> 25:59.591
[overlapping chatter]

26:07.399 --> 26:09.668
[Maria sniffling]

26:40.565 --> 26:42.033
What's on your mind, Mom?

27:47.832 --> 27:49.534
- [loud bang]
- [gasps]

28:03.314 --> 28:04.916
[printer whirring]

28:28.239 --> 28:30.842
ZETA: What the hell
are you doing here?

28:34.713 --> 28:36.614
You're not to blame
for what Morte did.

28:36.681 --> 28:40.318
What do you know?
You don't have a fucking clue.

28:40.385 --> 28:43.254
- Tell me then.
- Tell you what? Huh?

28:43.321 --> 28:44.756
That I could have prevented
all this?

28:44.823 --> 28:47.792
That I should have killed him
when I had the opportunity?

29:00.972 --> 29:03.108
Do you remember...

29:03.208 --> 29:05.009
the World Cup card collection?

29:05.677 --> 29:08.012
The one from '86?

29:11.449 --> 29:14.185
Hugo Sánchez was the best card
in the whole collection.

29:15.453 --> 29:17.889
I remember I never won anything,

29:17.956 --> 29:19.991
nor the popsicle sticks.

29:20.091 --> 29:20.892
Not even the yogurt lids.

29:22.961 --> 29:25.263
Suddenly, one day I won,

29:25.363 --> 29:27.732
the best fucking card
of the entire collection.

29:27.799 --> 29:29.934
No one in town had it,

29:30.001 --> 29:32.103
and I remember
that I came home

29:32.203 --> 29:34.038
screaming out loud
with excitement.

29:38.676 --> 29:40.278
I didn't see it coming.

29:42.147 --> 29:45.183
He kicked me really hard
against the stove.

29:47.786 --> 29:49.487
I was nine years old.

29:52.791 --> 29:55.894
And then, he grabbed my arm

29:55.960 --> 29:59.364
and shoved it
into the fire.

29:59.430 --> 30:02.400
"This way, you'll learn
not to scream," he said.

30:02.467 --> 30:04.435
You didn't say anything
to your mom?

30:08.373 --> 30:11.276
I went to the sink
and put my arm under water.

30:12.811 --> 30:14.412
Then I saw the knife.

30:16.281 --> 30:19.851
I went into his room,
and I wanted to stab him.

30:22.053 --> 30:25.023
That swine was snoring
and drooling

30:25.123 --> 30:25.890
like he always does.

30:30.829 --> 30:33.064
I should have stabbed him.

30:36.634 --> 30:38.369
I was a coward, Alvaro.

30:40.972 --> 30:43.241
[sobbing]

31:00.992 --> 31:04.929
I was a damn
motherfucking coward.

31:04.996 --> 31:07.265
[sobbing]

31:16.474 --> 31:18.076
And I still am.

31:21.913 --> 31:23.648
[door closes]

31:29.654 --> 31:31.022
I gotta bounce.

32:03.388 --> 32:05.123
- Hello?
- Hi, good afternoon.

32:05.189 --> 32:07.692
- Yes?
- I'd like to talk to Costa.

32:07.759 --> 32:10.361
Shouldn't we go with her?

32:10.428 --> 32:13.765
The thing is, I've been doing
some research on my own...

32:16.634 --> 32:18.069
It's best not to.

32:34.118 --> 32:35.553
Please, wait here.
I'll try to find Costa, okay?

32:35.653 --> 32:36.921
All right, thank you.

32:50.868 --> 32:51.869
I don't get it.

32:55.840 --> 32:57.041
I mean, he can't...

33:20.665 --> 33:22.567
Hello.

33:22.633 --> 33:23.868
What can I do for you?

33:40.752 --> 33:41.986
Is that the cop from Madrid?

33:46.557 --> 33:48.960
Cowabunga, dude.

34:01.372 --> 34:01.873
Something's wrong.

34:06.244 --> 34:07.678
QUINO: Hey, wait!

34:40.611 --> 34:42.947
[car starting]

34:48.453 --> 34:50.788
[tires screeching]

34:55.092 --> 34:57.495
♪♪♪

35:52.483 --> 35:55.386
WOMAN: You deserve to die!
You deserve to die!

35:55.486 --> 35:58.322
[overlapping shouting]

36:03.961 --> 36:06.964
[overlapping shouting continues]

36:13.371 --> 36:14.705
We hate you!

36:14.805 --> 36:18.009
[overlapping shouting continues]

36:22.413 --> 36:24.315
[overlapping shouting stops]

36:39.430 --> 36:42.867
I tried to speak to her father,
but he wasn't home.

36:50.041 --> 36:50.908
Mario!

36:56.914 --> 36:56.948
Mario?

37:10.361 --> 37:11.662
No.

37:12.964 --> 37:14.232
Mario.

37:17.034 --> 37:19.003
REPORTER:The disturbing
discovery of the remains...

37:19.070 --> 37:20.404
- Shit. No. -<i> ...of the three</i>
<i>Almanzora</i>

37:20.471 --> 37:22.707
<i>girls in a freezer has
been the news of the day</i>

37:22.807 --> 37:24.408
<i>as you all must
know by now.</i>

37:24.475 --> 37:27.912
<i>This live transmissionis
coming to you from Almanzora</i>

37:28.012 --> 37:31.015
<i>right outside
the police headquarters,</i>

37:31.082 --> 37:33.251
<i>where the main suspect
in this terrible case</i>

37:33.317 --> 37:36.854
<i>is actually being transferred
to prison as we speak.</i>

38:05.182 --> 38:07.251
[liquid sloshing]

38:07.318 --> 38:08.486
[lighter clicking]

38:11.055 --> 38:13.424
[people shouting]

38:35.846 --> 38:37.848
[tires screeching]

38:39.317 --> 38:42.787
♪♪♪

39:49.453 --> 39:52.623
No. Mario.

39:54.024 --> 39:54.091
Mario!
[banging]

40:02.366 --> 40:04.769
Mario?

40:07.071 --> 40:08.105
Mario!

40:33.164 --> 40:34.165
Mario!

40:37.067 --> 40:38.235
Mario!

40:55.519 --> 40:56.887
Come on, Mario.

41:11.268 --> 41:12.570
- [coughing]
PAULA: Mario.

41:12.636 --> 41:14.371
- Mario!
- Mario. Mario.

41:15.573 --> 41:16.640
Mario!

41:18.509 --> 41:20.611
Are you okay?
Are you okay?

41:21.712 --> 41:23.147
Are you okay?

41:23.247 --> 41:24.482
Are you crazy?

41:29.553 --> 41:33.123
Mario, look at me.

41:33.190 --> 41:36.994
It wasn't her.
It wasn't Sandra.

41:37.094 --> 41:40.197
She's not dead.
It's not them.

41:41.365 --> 41:43.667
There are many things
that I'm missing

41:43.767 --> 41:46.003
and I don't know how to explain,

41:46.070 --> 41:48.305
but-- but it can't be her.

41:48.405 --> 41:50.407
Because they need her.

41:50.474 --> 41:52.443
Costa,
Costa, I saw her.

41:52.510 --> 41:53.711
I saw her.

41:55.613 --> 41:57.147
Are you sure it was her?

41:57.248 --> 41:58.749
Really?

42:00.518 --> 42:02.987
Sandra is still alive.

42:03.087 --> 42:05.756
My gut is telling me so.

42:05.856 --> 42:08.993
But the ones behind this
want us to believe otherwise.

42:09.093 --> 42:10.394
[sniffling]

42:15.799 --> 42:18.235
Don't ever do this
to me again, you hear me?

42:22.673 --> 42:24.642
[sobbing]

42:25.943 --> 42:28.045
Can we call when we get there?

42:32.583 --> 42:34.919
I'm pretty sure Bea
got in the last bus.

42:42.693 --> 42:44.595
You missed the exit
to the spa.

42:53.237 --> 42:54.772
[sobbing]

42:54.838 --> 42:56.473
Where are you taking me?

42:58.075 --> 42:59.810
Please, help me.

42:59.877 --> 43:01.245
Where are you taking me?

43:12.389 --> 43:15.359
[ambulance doors closing,
engine starting]

43:35.012 --> 43:36.647
You were right, Mario.

43:39.316 --> 43:41.652
Macastre, Ontinyent, Alcoy--

43:41.719 --> 43:44.488
all the cases are connected,
there's a pattern.

43:44.555 --> 43:47.725
Every three years,
three teenagers disappear,

43:47.791 --> 43:49.994
and every three years,
the plagues.

43:50.094 --> 43:52.296
Always on the same dates.

43:52.363 --> 43:56.066
The moths, rats, seagulls.

43:56.166 --> 43:57.668
They say when
a tsunami's coming,

43:57.768 --> 43:59.670
the animals flee
to higher ground.

43:59.770 --> 44:02.039
Well, it's the same thing here,
I think.

44:02.106 --> 44:03.707
They sense danger coming,
a predator.

44:03.807 --> 44:07.011
None of what you say
makes any sense.

44:07.077 --> 44:09.813
I am convinced that Morte
is just an enforcer.

44:09.880 --> 44:11.649
He's just a scapegoat.

44:17.488 --> 44:19.957
Come on, Costa,
you fucking nailed it.

44:20.024 --> 44:22.192
They shave their heads,
they force them to eat bugs.

44:22.292 --> 44:25.562
This time, something went wrong
and Malena died,

44:25.629 --> 44:28.065
and that's why they needed
another girl to replace her.

44:30.000 --> 44:31.935
Whatever it is that
they wanna do with the girls

44:32.002 --> 44:33.504
is about to happen.

44:33.604 --> 44:36.173
The problem is that we have
no clue where they are,

44:36.240 --> 44:38.108
and that's what
we need to find out.

44:45.149 --> 44:48.052
♪♪♪

45:17.147 --> 45:18.649
I don't know, Costa,
what if you're wrong?

45:18.716 --> 45:20.050
What if I'm not?

45:20.117 --> 45:21.985
I think it's worth a try,
don't you?

45:24.288 --> 45:27.091
We have nothing more
to lose, Mario.

45:27.157 --> 45:28.892
What do you think
they want to do with her?

45:30.527 --> 45:32.663
That, I don't know.
But what I do know

45:32.763 --> 45:33.964
is that all the kids
have something in common.

45:36.667 --> 45:38.335
They're all 15 years old.

45:47.244 --> 45:49.079
And Zhou's at least 100.

45:59.923 --> 46:03.227
No!
Please, don't hurt me.

46:03.327 --> 46:04.928
No, no, no,
please, sir.

46:04.995 --> 46:06.597
Don't do this!

46:06.663 --> 46:09.233
Help me!
Please, help me!

46:09.333 --> 46:11.869
No, no, no.
No, please don't hurt me.

46:11.969 --> 46:14.872
I beg you, no.
No!

46:16.240 --> 46:18.776
Please, help me!
Somebody!

46:23.280 --> 46:25.182
Ah!

46:27.684 --> 46:28.385
[gunshot]
Help me!

46:28.485 --> 46:31.488
Please, don't.

46:31.555 --> 46:31.889
[gunshot]

47:23.073 --> 47:25.075
You don't have
to do this, sir.

47:39.890 --> 47:42.226
[high-pitch ringing]

47:59.843 --> 48:01.945
♪♪♪
